January 30, 1956. No. 13,

Original.

Wisconsin v. Tennessee. Vernon W. Thomson, Attorney General, argued the cause for the State of Wisconsin, plaintiff. With him on the brief were Stewart O. Honeck, Deputy Attorney General, and Roy G. Tulane and George F. Sieker, Assistant Attorneys General. Knox Bigham, Assistant Attorney General, argued the cause for the State of Tennessee, defendant. With him on the brief *956were George F. McCanless, Attorney General, Allison B. Humphreys, Jr., Solicitor General, and James M. Glasgow, Assistant Attorney General.

*955On motion for leave to file complaint. Argued January 23,1956. Decided January 30, 1956.

Per Curiam:

The motion for leave to file the complaint is denied.

Mr. Justice Harlan took no part in the consideration or decision of this motion.
